[{"caption":"3 Facts For Our Acts with Ilona ‚Äì merchandiser / @ilona_am_merch 

How did you become a merchandiser and when did you start? What skills do you absolutely have to have for the job?
I.: I just slipped into it. An old acquaintance once asked if I had time, and if I could imagine helping to sell the merch at a big show. I could, and so it happened. The ‚Äúonly‚Äù thing was just to do merch for Phil Collins at a stadium show. That had of course nothing to do with the merch jobs that I knew from the punk rock shows so far.

What is the ratio of cash to digital payment methods and are there regional differences?
I.: At the shows I do merch it is very different. It also depends on the genre. People increasingly pay by card. The young generation in particular pays by card. They hardly know cash anymore. Many in the ‚Äûolder‚Äú age simply don‚Äôt even know that this is possible at all and are always very happy when I tell them that card payment also works. But there is also the older generation that swears by ‚Äûonly cash is true‚Äú. I tell you, if I would get 5 ‚Ç¨ every time I hear that saying, I would have a nice pocket money.

What does a typical tour day look like for you as a merchandiser? What makes this job so appealing to you?
I.: Breakfast, shower, load in, set-up, restocking, making everything pretty, instructing helpers, doors open, show, sometimes restocking, sale, count out, cash register recount, dismantling, load out, shower, bed - that‚Äôs a day in fast running.
Since I‚Äôve always liked to go to concerts, liked to travel, liked to chat with people and organized some things, this job is like a surprise egg for me. I have all that in this job and besides, I have 99 % only happy people around me. Nobody goes to a concert when people don‚Äôt feel like it. And the crews are usually always awesome. We always have a lot of fun on tour and laugh a lot. When you‚Äôre on tour for a longer period of time and share a nightliner with 18 people, it‚Äôs a great feeling of community. People look out for each other and show consideration. I have never experienced this in my 9 to 5 jobs among colleagues like this. It‚Äôs a very special kind of work, even if we have incredibly long days.","comments":6,"datetime":"2025-03-09T08:40:44.000Z","id":"3584365149003203704","image_url":"https://scontent-fra5-2.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.2885-15/482901117_17952268724937247_8769971459589158509_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e15_tt6&_nc_ht=scontent-fra5-2.cdninstagram.com&_nc_cat=107&_nc_oc=Q6cZ2QFnj8NKAkSlrpq1Cw2IhXyByIoNylbjTeQZzRVUcxa0kUAwKXK1iIxjcGWj6sbxnKM&_nc_ohc=q5bUK0raaVYQ7kNvwGTdM-n&_nc_gid=uh8afSDDbH9LwBPNgvqUlw&edm=AOQ1c0wBAAAA&ccb=7-5&oh=00_AfSrFv-u6r0Do7P9jxpPMQKdNF512srcoQrpP0aihbJWqw&oe=6878E199&_nc_sid=8b3546","likes":111,"content_type":"GraphImage","url":"https://www.instagram.com/p/DG-ORy7oER4","video_url":null,"is_pinned":false}]

R.M.F.C. (or Rock Music Fan Club) is the bedroom recording project of New South Wales teen Buz Clatworthy.
This fits nicely alongside any of the recent spate of releases from fellow NWI-worshiping Aussies, like Satanic Togas, Research Reactor Corp, Disco Junk, Gee Tee, etc.
What sets R.M.F.C. apart from those other bands is the willingness to slow things down a bit. While there are plenty of the lightning-fast tracks that you‚Äôve probably come to expect from this lot, songs like ‚ÄúTelevision‚Äù and ‚ÄúMirror‚Äù creep by in comparison and really allow you the time to appreciate the odd mix of influences the band is working with.

REPLICANT set themselves apart from the pack by honing their brand of unorthodox death metal laden with technicality, dissonance, and atmosphere, marinated in an unhealthy dousing of groove. At times progressive, but unapologetically regressive, the forward-thinking collective have been twisting the concept of technical death metal since their inception in 2014.

We probably had the weirdest day in our band's history!

Yesterday BUMA/Stemra, the Dutch performing rights association, released their 2023 music export report. They put us on the 5th position as the only band in the top 10. The other 9 are mostly millionaire DJs. So we are sticking out like a sore thumb, which triggers national media to write about this band they have never heard of. We are being featured on TV and radio shows, the national news, in the big newspapers; shit's really been hitting the fan!

Ironically, this made us postpone our tour announcement for some days. Apologies for that, it's coming soon!

[{"caption":"‚Ä¢ 19.05.25 ‚Ä¢

Doors: 19:00
Start: 20:00 (!)

...in Trier - @villawuller 

A show on a Monday is the best way to start a week. Show up, bring your friends and support your local DIY scene!

@joliettemx (Post Hardcore/Screamo, Mexico City)

Originally from the city of Puebla but currently reside in Mexico City. They have a complex sound that is hard to fit within the boundaries of a genre. Blending influences that range from post-hardcore, math rock, and screamo to different styles of metal; they manage deliver a sound that is equally captivating and energetic. The commitment of the four-piece is not only reflected on their compelling, sometimes proggy songwriting tendencies, but also on their work ethic, extensive touring, and an extraordinarily impassioned live show. The sound of the band has been evolving along with them since their inception in 2010. Their 2011 debut EP, "Convertirse en Agua", featured a young and earnest band that started gathering a small fanbase. They released a second EP the year later titled "Voltean/Estan Felices", which helped them further develop their sound and start playing shows outside the city of Puebla. In 2013 they released their acclaimed debut LP, "Principia", and established themselves as one of the most exciting new bands to come out of the Latin American scene. For their 2016 sophomore album, "At√°xico", they took their sound to a new level and released their most aggressive, chaotic, and dissonant work to date. After a few years that saw them tour relentlessly around the world, they recorded their third and currently last LP titled "Luz Devora", their most focused and mature release so far. With their stunning last 2 singles, "Contraluz" and "Segundero", joliette prove that they are a band that's never going to stop getting better with the years. They have developed their music into a style of their own, and that opens the possibilities for very electrifying releases in the future.

@dispassionatehc (Emotional Hardcore, Trier/SB)

We couldn't have wished for a better band to complete this evening. These local legends are some of our closest friends. Rumor has it that new recordings will be released sometime this yearüëÄ","comments":1,"datetime":"2025-04-23T16:11:28.000Z","id":"3617206914665153068","image_url":"https://scontent-fco2-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.2885-15/491439001_18060988454026989_2760553584882893509_n.webp?stp=dst-jpg_e35_p1080x1080_sh0.08_tt6&_nc_ht=scontent-fco2-1.cdninstagram.com&_nc_cat=109&_nc_oc=Q6cZ2QEp8EZUqoBD9WW9MqHpAQNCaZs6UWFqsmBHTq0EUdWXFb04XofIu6-iV7hnsnRDaC4&_nc_ohc=ptisMcvM5AwQ7kNvwGCD56U&_nc_gid=MlJX1HF8ZOi7MuuT7V8CLA&edm=AOQ1c0wBAAAA&ccb=7-5&oh=00_AfSeGLJdGO-lEWToSrCzuZZU77nUIPyRotbgqhQg2qydhA&oe=6878D42B&_nc_sid=8b3546","likes":167,"location":{"has_public_page":true,"id":"10152192","name":"villaWuller","slug":"villawuller"},"content_type":"GraphSidecar","url":"https://www.instagram.com/p/DIy5oYrtAIs","video_url":null,"is_pinned":false},{"caption":"‚Ä¢ 01.07.24 ‚Ä¢

@yourarmsaremycocoon 
@awakebutstillinbed
@dispassionatehc 

@villawuller 

It's been a week now and we're still trying to process what exactly happened. 

Three of our absolute favorite bands in what is effectively our living room, the @villawuller - an evening we won't be able to forget anytime soon. Wonderful music, and even more wonderful people.

Special thanks to @dispassionatehc for your tireless support. Without you we wouldn't have been able to put on such a great evening and without you the evening would've only been half as nice. We are infinitely happy to have such talented friends with an amazing band in our neighborhood and are very much looking forward to finally hearing the new recordings soon.

Before we started this concert group, we would have had to drive several hundred kilometers for a lineup like this. Thanks to everyone who supports our little DIY shows - we don't take it for granted! It's a lot of work and we don't earn any money with these shows. We're just happy whenever we don't have to pay for anything with our private savings. But evenings like these are the reason why it's all worth it <3

Let's not let Trier degenerate into an ever-aging tourist tomb and get actively involved or support subcultural places away from commercial pressures.

biography: Stories of light, people and places.
posts:
[{"caption":"Waiting for sunset, March 2025 

In March this year, I had the opportunity to travel to India as part of a trip organized by @photowalk.podcast. Together with a group of talented photographers, we explored markets, traveled by train, visited landmarks, and participated in the Holi festival.

With my European appearance, it was difficult not to be spotted by the locals while wandering around the various locations, no matter how large the crowds around me. More than once, I was asked for selfies by them, and instead of documenting scenes undisturbed, I ended up chatting with the people I met. And even in moments when we didn't share a common language, there was always this communication through gestures or smiles that expressed mutual interest in the other person. Over the next weeks I will share images testament to these connections, for which I am very grateful.

In March this year, I had the opportunity to travel to India as part of a trip organized by @photowalk.podcast. Together with a group of talented photographers, we explored markets, traveled by train, visited landmarks, and participated in the Holi festival.

With my European appearance, it was difficult not to be spotted by the locals while wandering around the various locations, no matter how large the crowds around me. More than once, I was asked for selfies by them, and instead of documenting scenes undisturbed, I ended up chatting with the people I met. And even in moments when we didn't share a common language, there was always this communication through gestures or smiles that expressed mutual interest in the other person. Over the next weeks I will share images testament to these connections, for which I am very grateful.

We hit play on "UNIT3" by @infinaofficial x @slatz_music and instantly felt it:
That perfect blend of metal trap and rap‚Äîthe kind that kicks the door in and dares you to listen.

It‚Äôs more than a sound.
It‚Äôs a warning. A war cry. A wake-up call.

This track is for the ones who‚Äôve been told to sit down, shut up, and stay small.
It‚Äôs about refusing that script.
About unifying when the world wants us divided.
About thinking for yourself when the system‚Äôs banking on you staying asleep.

UNIT3 doesn‚Äôt hold back.
It throws fists, bars, and breakdowns straight at the forces that want us numb.
And somehow‚Ä¶ it makes you feel more alive than ever.

This isn‚Äôt just metal.
This is movement.

Die letzten Jahre haben eine Menge Kraft gekostet. Und wir haben auch gemerkt, dass wir unsere Energie auf andere Themen fokussieren wollen, die nichts mit der Band zu tun haben. Wir haben in 21 Jahren Bandgeschichte nicht eine l√§ngere Pause eingelegt und hatten den Fu√ü immer auf dem Gaspedal. Das gr√∂√üte Dankesch√∂n geht aber an euch - unsere Unterst√ºtzer*innen, Fans, Weggef√§hrten, Besucher*innen: Wir sind euch f√ºr immer dankbar.

Mit euch wollen wir nochmal gemeinsam abdampfen und zusammen den Hund begraben. Wir wollen mit euch eine grandiose letzte Runde drehen und gemeinsam die N√§gel in den Sarg hauen.

NOISE FOR THE VOICELESS is a Berlin-based rapcore band founded in 2022, giving a voice to the unheard. Am 07. August kommt meine neue Single TREIBSAND raus.
Das ist zwar noch ewig hin, aber ich kann es nicht mehr geheim halten.
Den Song hab ich in zwei Versionen aufgenommen. 
Einmal als volle Punk Rock Nummer mit Drums und E Gitarre. Hauptgrund daf√ºr ist, dass ich sau gerne meine @hagstrom_guitars Viking spiele um Songs zu schreiben und manchmal gehen da die Pferde mit mir durch üòÖ
Die andere Version ist eine Akustik Band Version. Mit Akustikgitarre, Mandoline, Kontrabass. Irgendwo zwischen Folkpunk und Bluegrass. 
Normalerweise gibt's dann ja ne "richtige" Version und eine "alternative" Version - das will ich aber eben nicht.
Beide Versionen sind v√∂llig gleichberechtigt und sind dabei Ausdruck von Folk und Punk - die beiden Elemente von Satz Mit X. 
.
Etwas treibt sich um. Treibsand.
